1. Liberia's flag is quite similar to that of the United States of America
except with 11 stripes instead of 13, and 1 large, centered star instead of 50
2. Liberia was originally for freed slaves who could find a place to be free from slavery.
3. Liberia is known for being one of the only countries in Africa, along with Ethiopia, 
that were never colonized by Europeans.
4. The national animal of Liberia is the Asiatic lion. This cat goes by many names, also known as
the Persian or Indian lion.
5. In Liberia's Sapo National Park, you can find the pygmy hippopotamus, pangolins, leopards,
and so many more interesting creatures!
6.